metadata.name: Nounfall #260
metadata.description:
Nounfall is drawn exclusively from the 234 heads and 21 glasses that are used to build the current Nouns collection. The background colors are all pulled from the blessed Noun palette.

This is ok because Nouns are CC0, which basically means public domain. Check out nouns.wtf for more info.

They make for fun social media banners when cropped, if you wanna show off you fandom of Nouns.

C : Clear screen and start animation over
S : Save current image
1 -> 6 : Set pixel density to the respective number

So, if you want a high resolution file, tap `6` for it to redraw, and then `S` to save. You can also save while it's animating if you like, which is fun too.

metadata.name: Aurora Solitude (Collectors Only Edition) #31
metadata.description:
"Aurora Solitude" is an exploration of my love for crystals, architecture, being one with nature, escaping technology and becoming ok with the idea of being alone. The series was derived using diffusion Ai models and put together in a generative image composition on fx(hash).

June 2022
198 editions were made available to current collectors.
Remaining unclaimed editions will be burned.

metadata.description:

62 layer.

Canvas 256x256(1024x1024)


For screen shot, open it Pixel Seascapes in new tab via fxHash button. And press("S") to take (1024x1024) screen shot.

metadata.name: Colorful Cubes #64
metadata.description:
This work of art is a painting that has been designed using mathematical algorithms. In this work, various color palettes have been used.

The buyer of the work can prepare this work in large sizes and print it on paper or canvas.

To save as a png file, press the following keys:
- [s] for a 2000*2000 pixel image
- [m] for a 4000x4000 pixel image
- [l] for a 8000x8000 pixel image

--
Artist: Pointiago
Jun 09, 2022
License: NFT 2.0

metadata.name: In The Distance - Tree Brush #14
metadata.description:
In the Distance is a clean, colorful, textural abstract that features a bold, dramatic sky above an outstretched volume. A hint of recursive trees form a line that traces the horizon.

Vibrant colors add a sense of fantasy to the generative realm.

Created using p5.js. Cover pages created using select iterations.

Press the Down Arrow to save the frame as a png.
Click or Tap the canvas to toggle full screen.

metadata.name: Snapshots from the land of 1000 towers #3
metadata.description:
For the love of Art and jumping in rain puddles ^__^

mouse-click switches between: 
- screen scaled image.
- full image :right-click: save/copy this one for all the pixels; can be tricky sometimes ^__^

The scaled image will reset after some time, with a new drawing.


xxx Amsterdam chill-out

vanilla javascript, the 3D is all programmed in plain javascript; 
so it might run on older devices as well. total pixel-control .__0
I love work that changes after some time, I guess it has to do with; that I vj'd at parties/clubs; showing visuals.

Some more information in the source-code.

Reserves will be freed in the next 3 days.
